                <h2>Clinical Treatments — When Natural Remedies Are Not Enough</h2>
                <p>Natural remedies can slow the spread, but if greying is aggressive or has reached an advanced stage, clinical treatments deliver significantly better results. The following advanced treatments are available at DenceSpot Clinic Gurgaon:</p>

                <h3>PRP (Platelet-Rich Plasma) Therapy</h3>
                <p>In <a href="prp-hair-treatment-natural-way-to-regrow-hair.php">PRP treatment</a>, growth factors are extracted from your own blood and injected into the scalp. These growth factors can <strong>re-activate dormant melanocytes</strong>. Research shows that PRP stimulates melanocyte proliferation and migration. Noticeable improvement is typically seen after 4 to 6 sessions at monthly intervals. This is <a href="../hair-prp-treatment-in-gurgaon">DenceSpot's most popular anti-greying treatment</a>.</p>

                <h3>Growth Factor Therapy</h3>
                <p>Concentrated growth factors are delivered directly into the scalp. These nourish melanocyte stem cells and extend their lifespan. When combined with PRP, the results are even more effective.</p>

                <h3>Mesotherapy for Anti-Greying</h3>
                <p>Mesotherapy involves delivering a cocktail of vitamins, minerals, amino acids, and peptides into the scalp through micro-injections. This delivers nutrients directly to the melanocytes — making it far more effective than oral supplements since absorption is 100%. The cocktail typically includes copper peptides, Vitamin B complex, and biotin.</p>

                <h3>LED Light Therapy</h3>
                <p>Specific wavelengths of red and near-infrared light can stimulate melanocyte function. This treatment is non-invasive, painless, and is used as a complement to PRP. Weekly sessions produce cumulative results over time.</p>

                <h2>Anti-Greying Supplements — Do They Actually Work?</h2>
                <p>There are many "anti-grey" supplements available on the market. Here is a look at which ones are actually supported by evidence:</p>

                <p><strong>Catalase supplements:</strong> The catalase enzyme neutralizes hydrogen peroxide. Some studies suggest that supplementation may slow greying. <strong>PABA (Para-Aminobenzoic Acid):</strong> A B-vitamin complex that has been found helpful in reversing greying in certain studies. <strong>Copper supplements:</strong> These should only be taken if a blood test confirms copper deficiency — excess copper is toxic. <strong>Fo-Ti (He Shou Wu):</strong> This herb has been used in Chinese medicine for centuries to combat greying. Some preliminary research supports its efficacy. <strong>Biotin + B12 combination:</strong> Together, these two nutrients support the melanin production pathway.</p>

                <p><strong>Important warning:</strong> Do not take any supplement without consulting a doctor. Over-supplementation can be harmful. At DenceSpot, we review your blood reports and then recommend a specific supplement plan tailored to your needs.</p>

                <h2>Realistic Timeline — What to Expect and When</h2>
                <p>To be completely honest — <strong>hair that has already turned white reverting to black is quite rare</strong>. The question of whether <a href="can-white-hair-turn-black-again.php">white hair can turn black again</a> has a complicated answer. While it is possible in some cases, for the majority, the focus should be on preventing further spread.</p>

                <p><strong>Month 1-2:</strong> The effects of dietary changes and supplements begin to build up in the body. Natural remedies start improving scalp health. If clinical treatments are initiated, the initial response begins to appear.</p>

                <p><strong>Month 3-4:</strong> New hair growth shows better pigment retention. The speed of spreading should begin to slow. Noticeable improvement in scalp health becomes evident. Blood reports start showing correction of deficiencies.</p>

                <p><strong>Month 5-6:</strong> If a consistent approach has been followed, the spread should have slowed significantly. PRP results become clearly visible. Some individuals report darker pigment in newly grown hair.</p>

                <p><strong>Month 6+:</strong> This is the maintenance phase — focused on sustaining results. Quarterly PRP sessions are recommended. Continued dietary discipline is essential. Natural remedies serve as ongoing support.</p>

                <p>It is important to understand that greying is an <strong>ongoing process</strong>. It cannot be "cured," but it can definitely be <strong>slowed and managed</strong>. Those who remain consistent achieve dramatically better results compared to those who try for a month or two and then give up.</p>

